{"title": "Biden approved secret nuclear strategy focusing on Chinese threat, New York Times reports", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2024-08-21", "content": "WASHINGTON - US President Joe Biden approved in March a highly classified nuclear strategic plan that for the first time reoriented Washington's deterrent strategy towards China's expansion of its nuclear arsenal, the New York Times reported on Aug 20.\nThe White House never announced that Mr Biden had approved the revised strategy, titled the \"Nuclear Employment Guidance,\" the newspaper reported.\nAn unclassified notification to Congress of the revision is expected to be sent before Mr Biden leaves office, the newspaper reported.\nIn recent speeches, two senior administration officials were allowed to allude to the strategy revision, the newspaper reported.\nThe strategy is updated every four years or so, the newspaper added.\nThe White House did not immediately respond to a request for comment on the report. REUTERS"}